# User Identity Ports — Architecture Guide

## Core Principle

`idpSub` (JWT `sub` claim) is **auth2-internal**. It is decoded in auth2, translated to `userId`
(app profile UUID) via `IUserLookupPort`, and **never passed raw to any other module**.
All domain modules use `userId` exclusively.

---

## Identity Field Convention

| Field | Type | Where | Who may use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `idpSub` | IdP subject (`JWT.idpSub`) | `AuthUser.idpSub` | auth2 guards, adapters, token-vault2 only |
| `userId` | App profile UUID | `AuthUser.userId` | All domain modules — audit fields, access control |
| `userInfo` | `UserInfo` (full profile) | `AuthUser.userInfo` | Any module needing display data from `AuthUser` |

---

## Three-Port Decision Guide

| Question | Answer |
|---|---|
| I need to look up a user by app UUID | Use `IUserLookupPort.findById(id)` |
| I need to look up multiple users by app UUIDs | Use `IUserLookupPort.findByIds(ids)` |
| I need to find a user by IdP subject (auth2 only) | Use `IUserLookupPort.findByIdPSub(idpSub)` |
| I need all members of a role | Use `IUserRolePort.findIdPSubsByRole(roleName)` → then `IUserLookupPort.findByIdPSubs(subs)` |
| I need to grant/revoke/list roles programmatically | Use `AuthFacade` — never call CommandBus directly |

---

## Port Locations

```
src/core/domain/ports/user-lookup.port.ts      ← IUserLookupPort + UserInfo (host app implements)
src/auth2/domain/ports/user-role.port.ts       ← IUserRolePort (AuthModule provides, do NOT implement in host)
src/auth2/application/services/auth.facade.ts  ← AuthFacade (AuthModule provides)
```

---

## What NOT to Do

```ts
// ❌ NEVER read user.idpSub outside auth2
const userId = user.idpSub;   // wrong — sub is opaque, use user.userId

// ❌ NEVER store idpSub in any audit field
createdById: user.idpSub     // wrong — ALWAYS use user.userId
updatedById: user.idpSub     // wrong — ALWAYS use user.userId

// ❌ NEVER fall back to idpSub when userId is unavailable
const auditId = caller.userId ?? caller.idpSub; // wrong — throw instead

// ❌ NEVER implement IUserRolePort in the host app
// IUserRolePort is provided by AuthModule — it queries authUserRole/authUserRoleGroup tables

// ❌ NEVER import Prisma types into IUserLookupPort
// The port returns UserInfo — a pure TypeScript interface with no Prisma dependency

// ❌ NEVER pass idpSub to correspondence2 or any other non-auth2 module
// All cross-module user references MUST use userId (app profile UUID)
```

---

## Correct Audit Field Pattern

`userId` must always be available by the time an authenticated request reaches a command handler.
If it is absent, the caller has a misconfigured module wiring — throw, never silently fall back.

```ts
// ✅ Controller helper — use this everywhere a userId is needed for audit
private requireUserId(caller: AuthUser): string {
  if (!caller.userId) {
    throw new Error(
      'userId not available on AuthUser — ensure UserModule is imported AFTER AuthModule',
    );
  }
  return caller.userId;
}

// ✅ Correct usage in controller actions
createUser(...) {
  return this.commandBus.execute(
    new CreateUserCommand({ ..., createdById: this.requireUserId(user) }),
  );
}

updateUser(...) {
  return this.commandBus.execute(
    new UpdateUserAdminCommand({ ..., adminId: this.requireUserId(user) }),
  );
}
```

### Naming convention for audit params in Commands

| Field | Carries | Previously (❌) | Now (✅) |
|---|---|---|---|
| `createdById` | userId of creator | `createdBySub` | `createdById` |
| `updatedById` / `adminId` / `requestorId` | userId of actor | `adminSub`, `requestorSub` | `adminId`, `requestorId` |

All command fields that represent "who performed this action" must end in `Id` and carry the app profile UUID, never the IdP subject.

---

## Consuming App — Registration Template

```ts
// UserModule (host app):
@Module({
  providers: [
    { provide: IUserLookupPort, useClass: UserAdapter },
  ],
  exports: [IUserLookupPort],
})
export class UserModule {}

// UserAdapter implements IUserLookupPort:
@Injectable()
export class UserAdapter implements IUserLookupPort {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  async findById(id: string): Promise<UserInfo | null> { ... }
  async findByIds(ids: string[]): Promise<UserInfo[]> { ... }
  async findByIdPSub(idpSub: string): Promise<UserInfo | null> { ... }
  async findByIdPSubs(idpSubs: string[]): Promise<UserInfo[]> { ... }
}

// AppModule — wire everything:
AuthModule.forRoot({ ... }), // registers IUserRolePort + AuthFacade automatically
UserModule,                   // registers IUserLookupPort
CorrespondenceModule.forRoot({ ..., imports: [AuthModule, UserModule] }),
```

---

## Caching Reference

| Call site | Cached? | Where |
|---|---|---|
| `UserAccessAdapter.resolve(idpSub)` → `IUserLookupPort.findByIdPSub` | Yes — TTL from `userAccessTtlMs` (default 30 min) | `CacheService` inside `UserAccessAdapter` |
| `ApiKeyVerifierAdapter.validate` | Yes — TTL from `apiKeyTtlMs` (default 30 min) | `CacheService` inside `ApiKeyVerifierAdapter` — `IUserLookupPort` not called |
| `SubscriptionResolutionService` dispatch path | No — hits port fresh per dispatch | Consuming app's `UserAdapter` may add own cache |
| `AuthFacade.getUsersByRole` | No | Consuming app's `UserAdapter` may add own cache |

---

## Breaking Changes (from old `sub`/`userSub` approach)

- `AuthUser.idpSub` → `AuthUser.idpSub` — update all `user.idpSub` reads
- `AuthUser.claims` → `AuthUser.idpClaims` — update all `user.claims` reads
- REST URL `auth2/rbac/users/:sub` → `auth2/rbac/users/:idpSub` — clients must update
- `UserRoleResponseDto.userSub` → `idpSub` — Swagger schema changed
- DB columns: `auth_user_role.userSub` → `idpSub`, `auth_user_role_group.userSub` → `idpSub` (migration required)
- `IUserQueryPort` and `USER_QUERY_PORT` are **removed** — replace with `IUserLookupPort` + `IUserRolePort`

---

## Justified Exceptions

- `token-vault2` uses `ownerSub` — IdP-bound by design, accepted exception
- Within `auth2` guards and adapters, `idpSub` is the local identifier — that is intentional
